claims:
Claims 1. A neural network (NN) processing element circuit for use in a NN processor for performing neural network calculations for an artificial neural network (ANN) having one or more network layers, comprising: a multiplier operative to receive weight and input data and to generate a product therefrom; an adder operative to receive and sum said product and a current context to generate an updated context therefrom; a local memory coupled to said adder and operative to store said updated context therein; and wherein individual storage locations in said local memory are accessed in a predefined manner other than randomly. 2. The circuit according to claim 1, wherein each storage location in said local memory represents at least one neuron in the ANN. 3. The circuit according to claim 2, further comprising circuitry operative to implement a plurality of logical neurons in a single neuron in said local memory, wherein each context represents the output of a single neuron, and wherein said logical neurons are time-multiplexed wherein each location in said local memory represents different neurons from a plurality of neurons at different times. 4. The circuit according to claim 1, wherein said local memory has a depth that reflects a number of simultaneous contexts the processing element can implement in a spatial domain. 5. The circuit according to claim 4, wherein the processing element can implement additional contexts in said local memory in a time domain by swapping out the contents thereof to memory located in a higher aggregation level. 6. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a first representation circuit operative to format weight and/or input data as integer or floating point representation before input to said multiplier. 7. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a second representation circuit operative to format products generated by said multiplier as integer or floating point representation before input to said adder. 8. The circuit according to claim 1, wherein said local memory is located within said processing element and dedicated for use therewith. 9. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a first multiplexer circuit operative to select between said current context stored in said local memory or a context stored in memory located in a higher aggregation level for input to said adder. 10. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a second multiplexer circuit operative to select between said updated context generated by said adder or a context stored in memory located in a higher aggregation level to be stored in said local memory. 11. The circuit according to claim 1 , further comprising a third multiplexer circuit operative to select between a function located at a higher aggregation level, memory located in a higher aggregation level, or said local memory to write said updated context generated by said adder. 12. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a plurality of multipliers and circuity operative to combine two or more multipliers capable of performing higher precision multiplications compared to a single multiplier. 13. The circuit according to claim 1, further comprising a quad circuit that combines four multipliers to yield a double precision processing element circuit. 14. A neural network (NN) processing element circuit for use in a NN processor for performing neural network calculations for an artificial neural network (ANN) having one or more network layers, comprising: a plurality of multipliers operative to multiply received weight and input data to generate a product therefrom; an accumulator operative to add said product with a current context received from either a local memory or memory located at a higher aggregation level to generate an updated context therefrom; said local memory coupled to said accumulator and operative to store said updated context therein in sequential fashion; 

 a multiplexer operative to write said updated context to either said local memory, said memory located at a higher aggregation level, or to a function located at a higher aggregation level, in accordance with a select control signal; and wherein individual storage locations in said local memory are accessed in a predefined manner other than randomly. 15. The circuit according to claim 14, wherein each storage location in said local memory represents at least one neuron in the ANN. 16. The circuit according to claim 14, wherein the processing element can implement additional contexts in said local memory in a time domain by swapping out the contents thereof to memory located in a higher aggregation level. 17. The circuit according to claim 14, further comprising a first representation circuit operative to format weight and/or input data as integer or floating point representation before input to said adder. 18. The circuit according to claim 14, further comprising a second representation circuit operative to format products generated by said multiplier as integer or floating point representation before input to said adder. 19. The circuit according to claim 14, further comprising a quad circuit that combines four multipliers to yield a double precision processing element circuit. 20. A method implemented by an integrated circuit (IC), the IC including a neural network (NN) processing element circuit for use in a NN processor for performing neural network calculations for an artificial neural network (ANN) having one or more network layers, the method comprising: multiplying ANN weight and input data to generate a product therefrom; summing said product and a current context to generate an updated context therefrom; storing said updated context in a memory local and dedicated to the processing element circuit; and wherein individual storage locations in said local memory are accessed in a predefined manner other than randomly. 21. The method according to claim 20, wherein each storage location in said local memory represents at least one neuron in the ANN. 22. The method according to claim 21, further comprising time-multiplexing said neurons in said local memory, wherein each location represents a different neuron from a plurality of neurons at different times. 23. The method according to claim 20, further comprising implementing additional contexts in said local memory in a time domain by swapping out the contents thereof to memory located in a higher aggregation level. 24. The method according to claim 20, further comprising formatting weight and/or input data as integer or floating point representation before said multiplication. 25. The method according to claim 20, further comprising formatting said product as integer or floating point representation before said summing. 26. The method according to claim 20, further comprising selecting between said current context stored in said local memory or a context stored in memory located in a higher aggregation level for input to said summing. 27. The method according to claim 20, further comprising selecting between said updated context generated by said summing or a context stored in memory located in a higher aggregation level to be stored in said local memory. 28. The method according to claim 20, further comprising selecting between a function located at a higher aggregation level, memory located in a higher aggregation level, or said local memory to write said updated context generated by said summing. 29. The method according to claim 20, further comprising combining four multiplier circuits to yield a double precision processing element circuit. 30. A method implemented by an integrated circuit (IC), the IC including a neural network (NN) processing element circuit for use in a NN processor for performing neural network calculations for an artificial neural network (ANN) having one or more network layers, the method comprising: receiving a first operand, a second operand, and a third operand; 

 dividing operation of said processing element circuit into time slots; performing computations involving said first operand, said second operand, and said third operand to generate an updated data element therefrom; storing said data element in a memory local and dedicated to the processing element circuit; wherein individual storage locations in said local memory are accessed in a predefined manner other than randomly; and wherein data elements are time-multiplexed with each location in said memory representing different data elements from a plurality of data elements at different times.
